<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880419-0191 </DOCNO><HL> Corning Glass Works Purchase </HL><SO> </SO><CO> GLW </CO><IN> TNM </IN><DATELINE> CORNING, N.Y.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Corning Glass Works said it acquired Saint-Amand Manufacturing Co., a closely held maker of disposable plastic pipettes for laboratory use. Terms weren't disclosed.    Corning purchased all of the San Fernando, Calif.-based company's shares outstanding from Elmer Saint-Amand and his wife, Deanna, who founded the company in 1971. Mr. Saint-Amand will be president of the new Corning subsidiary. Corning is a maker of specialty glass and ceramics, consumer housewares and telecommunication products, and provider of laboratory services. </TEXT></DOC>